    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It is so cold. Even with the hearth still glowing, I feel a chill that no fire can reach. Everyone keeps telling me to \"hold on,\" as if my hands aren't already trembling too much to grasp anything at all. They want me to endure, to prolong this slow, agonizing decay, but why? To live just to witness more betrayals? To exist as a hollow shell of who I once was? There is a stillness in the night that calls to me, a promise that the noise of this life can finally be silenced. It feels like the only honest thing left to do is to embrace the silence before it consumes me entirely.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
